Bedrock RAG Architecture:
- retrieve_and_generate API with HYBRID search, Haiku 4.5 generation
- DOC_REFS (RULE 8): <DOC_REFS>[JSON]</DOC_REFS> — mandatory, parsed by extract_doc_refs in bedrock_rag_service.rb
- Aurora cold-start: exponential backoff 15/30/45s in retrieve_and_generate_with_retry
- Chunk identity: **Document:** and **DOCUMENT_ALIASES:** headers in chunks (injected by Opus parsing)
- ChunkAliasExtractor uses `retrieve` API (vector only, no LLM) with metadata filter by S3 URI
- NEVER send images to LLM. Always S3 → KB → retrieve
- Reranker gated by BEDROCK_RERANKER_ENABLED env var (default off)
- session_context (from SessionContextBuilder) appended to generation prompt
- KB/bucket resolution: ENV → credentials.dig(:bedrock, ...) → defaults
- Stubs in tests: FakeBedrockAgentClient inner classes, define_singleton_method pattern (NO Mocha)

AWS KB Infrastructure (from kb:config):
- Vector store: Amazon Aurora PostgreSQL (RDS) — cold-start backoff applies
- Chunking: HIERARCHICAL (parent/child levels with overlap)
- Parsing: Opus foundation model with custom prompt (identity injection: DOCUMENT + DOCUMENT_ALIASES headers)
- Post-chunking: Lambda custom transformation injects [DOCUMENT:] and [SEARCH_ALIASES:] into each chunk
- Embedding: Titan Embeddings (dimensions configured in KB)
- Multimodal: supplemental S3 storage for image chunks
- Search: HYBRID (vector + keyword), configurable via BEDROCK_RAG_SEARCH_TYPE
